354
00:29:33,608 --> 00:29:36,369
So we are talking about 12 feet and not 10 feet.

355
00:29:40,811 --> 00:29:41,071
Right.

356
00:29:41,151 --> 00:29:44,693
But it is, you know, but that is, that is really a difference.

357
00:29:45,354 --> 00:29:53,238
So there's the friends of the community path and some of the other folks are hoping to

358
00:29:55,200 --> 00:30:13,691
put whatever pressure they can on the powers that be, including writing to all of the assorted elective offices and reaching out to DCR about this to try to figure out if there's a way to back up and redesign this to be wider.

359
00:30:15,752 --> 00:30:21,676
And I said that I would bring it to our meeting and see what

360
00:30:22,692 --> 00:30:29,317
the consensus here was before writing any letter like that.

361
00:30:31,659 --> 00:30:45,751
I think these really are competing interests in that on one hand, there's consequences for slowing it down, and there's consequences for waiting, and there's a really good argument for building it as fast as possible.

362
00:30:45,771 --> 00:30:49,954
And if that means living with the current design, that's what that means.

363
00:30:52,048 --> 00:30:57,611
There's also an argument for saying it's a big, expensive project and it should be future-proofed.

364
00:30:58,492 --> 00:31:14,842
And if we expect or hope for increased mode share and we expect more people are going to be on e-bikes and so forth, then it makes more sense to build it wider to start with than to regret

365
00:31:15,997 --> 00:31:17,498
how narrow it is later.

366
00:31:18,278 --> 00:31:24,061
And I think those are both good arguments.

