Yeah, and people tend to get a little snarky when they see the bike lane markings without the paved road.

1036
01:40:32,098 --> 01:40:32,399
Right.

1037
01:40:32,819 --> 01:40:33,159
It's true.

1038
01:40:38,231 --> 01:40:39,412
Do we have anything else?

1039
01:40:44,976 --> 01:40:52,242
I'm curious about the... Lily, you mentioned the Contraflow lane on South Street and the flex posts there.

1040
01:40:52,262 --> 01:40:57,886
I ride that a fair amount and I like it.

1041
01:40:57,906 --> 01:41:04,691
I think it works well, but most of the time when I've been riding eastbound, cars do use that

1042
01:41:06,099 --> 01:41:14,665
the north lane to pass, which works fine.

1043
01:41:14,685 --> 01:41:18,288
I mean, for me personally, like it doesn't feel that strange.

1044
01:41:18,428 --> 01:41:28,095
And sometimes I know people on bikes can feel a bit uncomfortable if it feels like they're clogging a lane and causing traffic to build up behind them.

1045
01:41:29,656 --> 01:41:32,317
I wonder if using lanes on, using,

1046
01:41:33,333 --> 01:41:46,721
Using the flex posts on South Street might end up making eastbound bike traffic feel a little more uncomfortable because they are going to be slowing down cars that might pull up behind them a bit.

1047
01:41:47,221 --> 01:41:56,347
Yeah, but I think that if we don't do that, cars are going to pass without looking for bikes in the oncoming lane.

1048
01:41:59,010 --> 01:42:17,304
I mean, that is a, people, there are a lot of places I can think of where people, I feel like people come, people are all of a, I'm all of a sudden have some car coming straight at me because they were passing somebody on the other side of the road and they didn't.

1049
01:42:19,446 --> 01:42:22,809
I'm also curious how people will,

1050
01:42:24,878 --> 01:42:28,581
behave in that spot once the bike markings are finally there.

1051
01:42:28,641 --> 01:42:34,705
There have been a couple of threads on Facebook where people are kind of freaking out and like, what are these random green boxes?

1052
01:42:34,765 --> 01:42:36,866
Why are they putting fake grass on the ground?

1053
01:42:37,747 --> 01:42:42,390
And there's been like green boxes for a pretty long time with no bike symbol in them.

1054
01:42:42,770 --> 01:42:47,273
And I know that's coming, but the random green boxes are really confusing to people.

1055
01:42:47,453 --> 01:42:47,693
And I'm

1056
01:42:48,594 --> 01:42:53,578
And I'm trying to reserve judgment until they actually have a bike symbol in them.

1057
01:42:54,279 --> 01:43:02,646
And then it becomes more clear that no, no, you bike in this direction on the lane and you bike in the bike lane going the other direction.

1058
01:43:04,567 --> 01:43:09,451
But that's not a separated two way bike lane that's separated from the.

1059
01:43:11,835 --> 01:43:16,999
Car lane, it's there's bike are allowed in both directions.

1060
01:43:17,619 --> 01:43:19,221
Cars are only allowed in one direction.

1061
01:43:23,310 --> 01:43:23,570
Right.

1062
01:43:23,790 --> 01:43:24,711
No, I totally hear you.

1063
01:43:24,771 --> 01:43:28,132
And Jared, I really do, I know what you're talking about.

1064
01:43:28,152 --> 01:43:34,254
I also use South Street in the non-contraflow direction.

1065
01:43:34,475 --> 01:43:38,276
And I've noticed a couple of times people have passed me by crossing that yellow line.

1066
01:43:38,316 --> 01:43:42,398
And the thought has occurred to me, you know, the same thought that had occurred to you, but I think,

1067
01:43:43,158 --> 01:43:48,040
what the city can do is really just see how things work and be responsive.

1068
01:43:48,080 --> 01:43:55,664
And if we're finding that there's a high level of discomfort there, and this is where feedback from you guys and anybody, you know, that uses it really, really helps us.

1069
01:43:56,304 --> 01:44:02,507
If we find that it's not working, we can kind of go back and reevaluate whether flex posts are a good idea in that situation.

1070
01:44:02,527 --> 01:44:04,968
I think ideally, you know, cars

1071
01:44:05,748 --> 01:44:12,812
get used to having bikes there and are following at a respectful distance because it's not super long of a street.

1072
01:44:12,932 --> 01:44:15,213
But I think that is important feedback to hear.

1073
01:44:15,273 --> 01:44:20,316
And we'll definitely keep that in mind as the facility, you know, as we roll things out with the flex posts.

1074
01:44:21,457 --> 01:44:22,697
Yeah, thank you.

1075
01:44:22,857 --> 01:44:27,680
I appreciate its effectiveness as a traffic calming measure for sure.

1076
01:44:28,280 --> 01:44:31,242
I just have heard like people feel some discomfort there with

1077
01:44:31,979 --> 01:44:39,794
It's like, oh, well, I don't care if they pass me, but I really don't like feeling like there's someone just like getting impatient right on my rear wheel.

1078
01:44:39,814 --> 01:44:42,659
It can just cause some discomfort there.

1079
01:44:42,720 --> 01:44:44,303
So just something to be on the lookout for.

1080
01:44:47,338 --> 01:44:58,346
Kevin Lily, what is the official like city policy about the movable crosswalk furniture.

1081
01:44:59,327 --> 01:45:05,131
In other words, the white flex posts on on the big on the hexagonal mats like.

1082
01:45:07,601 --> 01:45:11,584
I'm constantly sort of pushing them back towards the center line.

1083
01:45:12,405 --> 01:45:15,127
And like, is that what you're hoping for?

1084
01:45:18,890 --> 01:45:20,751
And, you know, how's that going?

1085
01:45:21,592 --> 01:45:22,413
That's a great question.

1086
01:45:23,313 --> 01:45:29,057
I don't know that we have an official policy on that, but we have observed that people often do move those things.

1087
01:45:29,918 --> 01:45:37,123
And, you know, if Todd or I or somebody else that kind of pays attention to these things are out and about and we find them in the wrong place, we will put them back.

1088
01:45:37,203 --> 01:45:41,405
And if you choose to do that, I think, you know, I don't think we have an official policy on that.

1089
01:45:41,826 --> 01:45:42,546
That sounds fine to me.

1090
01:45:43,667 --> 01:45:48,689
hypothesis about where I think they would go better than where I tend to find them.

1091
01:45:48,950 --> 01:45:49,810
Oh, I see.

1092
01:45:49,830 --> 01:45:53,031
In that case, you should probably email me or Todd and we can figure this out.

1093
01:45:53,051 --> 01:45:55,032
We kind of want to keep them where we've placed them.

1094
01:45:55,553 --> 01:46:04,917
But what I'm saying is sometimes people move them either out of the road because they don't like them, or we have had instances of people taking them so that they can use them for their own personal purposes.

1095
01:46:05,017 --> 01:46:05,738
It was both true.

1096
01:46:11,020 --> 01:46:20,993
sort of when the speed bump had just gone in on Winthrop Street at Playstead, and they were clearly there to keep people from going around the speed bump.

1097
01:46:22,976 --> 01:46:24,576
And they were slowly getting picked off.

1098
01:46:24,756 --> 01:46:32,420
I felt it was my job to re-soldier them as best as the remaining ranks could be deployed.

1099
01:46:34,141 --> 01:46:47,647
And same thing at Boston and High and the other ones that I'm in a lot where, you know, there's no longer an official marking on the ground, you know, that Todd would have.

1100
01:46:50,731 --> 01:47:02,010
And there are no longer as many as there originally were, but they still can fill their role of saying this is a crosswalk, you know, don't speed on the curb, kind of.

1101
01:47:03,760 --> 01:47:09,143
Yeah, I would say if you're putting them back where they are, you know, supposed to be that's that's great and we appreciate it.

1102
01:47:10,504 --> 01:47:14,726
We can't catch them all or kind of retrieve every single one.

1103
01:47:14,946 --> 01:47:23,310
If you have suggestions of where you think we should put them that somewhere else all together or that you think it would be more effective just email me or Todd and we'll take a look.

1104
01:47:24,414 --> 01:47:26,136
We have seen you go walking around.

1105
01:47:26,216 --> 01:47:33,422
I'm looking at the ones on Summer Street and Walnut Street, and I'm usually, I'm like, at the point when I pass them, I'm like almost home.

1106
01:47:33,482 --> 01:47:39,207
And most of the time I don't feel like stopping to put them back, but occasionally I do.

1107
01:47:39,227 --> 01:47:47,295
And they have also, you know, kind of gradually dwindled in number and have gotten less and less three-dimensional looking.

1108
01:47:48,725 --> 01:47:51,446
Are they officially a consumable in the city's budget?

1109
01:47:51,546 --> 01:47:54,286
Are they a capital or are they operating?

1110
01:47:56,247 --> 01:47:57,007
That's a great question.

1111
01:47:57,027 --> 01:47:59,948
I'm not sure, but we definitely need as many of them as we can get.

1112
01:48:00,028 --> 01:48:07,429
So we do try to preserve the limited assets that we have.

1113
01:48:08,750 --> 01:48:10,410
Well, they definitely seem to get consumed.

1114
01:48:13,432 --> 01:48:20,941
Sorry, we're talking about those movable bollard flex post things, not the indications that you have to stop for.

1115
01:48:20,961 --> 01:48:23,244
Those I know where they go.

1116
01:48:23,344 --> 01:48:24,245
It's the white flex posts.

1117
01:48:31,393 --> 01:48:42,258
I'll also say that the fact that you've deployed the full water-filled temporary Jersey barriers at Placedead and Winthrop is clearly the right solution there.

1118
01:48:42,278 --> 01:48:46,901
Because the little flex posts were just getting creamed.

1119
01:48:49,802 --> 01:48:50,983
Or thrown into the woods.

1120
01:48:53,144 --> 01:48:59,607
Yeah, those changes have caused a lot of whining from what I can tell from the general public and that sort of thing.

1121
01:49:00,565 --> 01:49:15,586
try to remind people that like there are growing pains associated with any change, even if it was to add five more lanes of traffic for the benefit of people in cars, you know, like any, any change is going to be problematic and any change that

1122
01:49:16,547 --> 01:49:31,531
isn't fully resolved yet right all the markings aren't there the signage isn't all there it's going to come with some confusion so like some patience is probably necessary and the fact that everything isn't perfect right at the beginning is not a sign of abject failure.

1123
01:49:32,023 --> 01:49:51,111
Yeah, I think along those lines, it's worth reminding everybody, every time that if you have it in you to go on Facebook or next door or any of those places where people flip out about whatever new thing painted on the road that they don't like.

1124
01:49:53,967 --> 01:50:06,690
Sometimes people just don't understand why things are done the way that they're done or that there's a process and it's really helpful to have kind of since you're here, you probably know more about the process than most people.

1125
01:50:07,891 --> 01:50:12,452
So just to show up and be a voice of reason in those places, even if it's just to say,

1126
01:50:13,569 --> 01:50:16,231
Hey, look, this is temporary and it's not finished yet.

1127
01:50:16,671 --> 01:50:27,560
Or this is, you know, this is temporary because X, Y, Z, or these are the considerations.

1128
01:50:27,580 --> 01:50:28,661
These are the constraints.

1129
01:50:28,741 --> 01:50:32,644
Yeah, it's, you know, there's,

1130
01:50:34,018 --> 01:50:37,780
this thing that you think they should have done and they were stupid for not doing this thing.

1131
01:50:37,840 --> 01:50:43,202
The reason they didn't do it is that the road is not physically wide enough to do that.

1132
01:50:43,263 --> 01:50:44,723
And it's not because they're idiots.

1133
01:50:45,584 --> 01:50:50,166
It's because they know something that you don't.

1134
01:50:50,206 --> 01:50:58,230
I think it is helpful to have, you know, just be the counter to the people freaking out about every new thing.

1135
01:51:00,540 --> 01:51:22,189
The other thing I want to say, the city, I think, or something is working on Winthrop Street, too, because I can identify, well, first, I recommend to others, I have been purposely changing my routine of where I bike for fun and exercise, and every other day, I am on Winthrop Street, and sometimes twice a morning.

1136
01:51:23,309 --> 01:51:28,190
Lupin, just to tell people that there are cyclists now in these lanes.

1137
01:51:30,331 --> 01:51:42,135
But I have also seen that people who used to park in front of their house in the bike lane have gotten the message from somebody somewhere that they should pull into their driveway.

1138
01:51:42,195 --> 01:51:46,056
And there was another one who was always parking in the crosswalk

1139
01:51:47,256 --> 01:51:48,657
right across from the synagogue.

1140
01:51:49,018 --> 01:51:51,819
And now that car is out of the crosswalk.

1141
01:51:52,220 --> 01:51:59,644
And like, that's, I'm just going to leave a note, didn't have to, I mean, it's working.

1142
01:52:00,525 --> 01:52:01,145
It's taking.

1143
01:52:01,165 --> 01:52:01,746
And

1144
01:52:05,868 --> 01:52:16,714
My other hero was the father who was leading his young son in the bike lane and they took the lane and they made the left into Victory Park, which is, that's ambitious.

1145
01:52:18,924 --> 01:52:19,624
But it should work.

1146
01:52:19,944 --> 01:52:23,147
But anyway, I just want to thank the city.

1147
01:52:23,348 --> 01:52:25,970
You know, I'm it's work.

1148
01:52:26,010 --> 01:52:31,415
And I think that trimming back those bushes as a code enforcement and that is 36 inches.

1149
01:52:32,976 --> 01:52:36,720
Leah.

1150
01:52:38,221 --> 01:52:41,624
For going around an obstruction, that's the.

1151
01:52:43,206 --> 01:52:44,026
minimum width.

1152
01:52:44,067 --> 01:52:45,587
Kind of the ADA minimum.

1153
01:52:45,707 --> 01:52:47,809
And if the overhang is, is, is.

1154
01:52:48,089 --> 01:52:50,190
The overhang I'm not sure about actually.

1155
01:52:50,210 --> 01:52:52,331
I've just seen sidewalk stuff.

1156
01:52:52,991 --> 01:52:57,654
I know I've seen something that's a guideline for overhangs too at some point.

1157
01:52:57,734 --> 01:53:02,757
I'm pretty sure there is one in some code, but I don't remember where.

1158
01:53:02,837 --> 01:53:05,959
The standard, like, um, um,

1159
01:53:08,229 --> 01:53:15,375
The US highway standard is eight feet off the sidewalk and 15 feet off the street or something like that.

1160
01:53:15,996 --> 01:53:21,681
And that's what the tree warden generally does if they're on site.

1161
01:53:22,021 --> 01:53:32,990
If you really want to dig into Massachusetts specifics, it's the Architectural Access Board and Massachusetts 521 CMR that govern like street ADA stuff.

1162
01:53:38,789 --> 01:53:42,331
I think it's getting to be time.

1163
01:53:42,351 --> 01:53:46,094
I'm getting messages that dinner is ready.

1164
01:53:46,114 --> 01:53:48,636
And, but I,

1165
01:53:52,906 --> 01:54:04,853
I hope that, I mean, I will say if it is actually obstructing the pathway enough that it's bothering anybody, then it probably is in violation of any ADA standard.

1166
01:54:04,973 --> 01:54:12,898
But the fact that it's in the way is proof enough that it needs to get turned back.

1167
01:54:14,419 --> 01:54:16,300
And I hope that that can happen.

1168
01:54:17,341 --> 01:54:18,882
Do we have anything else before we go?

1169
01:54:24,078 --> 01:54:46,052
I hate to be the person who's talking when it's nine o'clock, but back on the subject of grumpy people on Facebook, I feel like I don't... My general quibble with a lot of construction projects is that sometimes I feel like people have no way of...

1170
01:54:47,088 --> 01:54:48,369
knowing about them beforehand.

1171
01:54:48,409 --> 01:54:52,751
So it's kind of a foregone conclusion that they're going to get mad about it.

1172
01:54:52,891 --> 01:55:03,496
And like, if there was somehow the amount of resources to do like the outreach level that the big sweep does, like everyone knows about the big sweep.

1173
01:55:06,717 --> 01:55:07,217
Yeah, it does.

1174
01:55:07,257 --> 01:55:08,018
That's a good point.

1175
01:55:08,638 --> 01:55:12,840
Some of the people, it does seem like a lot of those conversations start out with,

1176
01:55:14,329 --> 01:55:16,130
well, how come nobody knew about it?

1177
01:55:16,190 --> 01:55:17,370
How come I didn't know about it?

1178
01:55:17,650 --> 01:55:21,992
And some of them are kind of like, well, I knew about it.

1179
01:55:22,272 --> 01:55:29,376
So the fact that you didn't know about it is- I knew about it, but I had to really pay attention to know about it.

1180
01:55:29,536 --> 01:55:30,316
Right.

1181
01:55:31,416 --> 01:55:31,997
And that's true.

1182
01:55:32,037 --> 01:55:43,462
And at the same time though, I don't think it's totally an unreasonable expectation that if you really wanna know about those things that you have to pay

1183
01:55:44,400 --> 01:55:46,400
closer than average attention.

1184
01:55:46,460 --> 01:55:51,421
Like there's only so many things that you can get through to people.

1185
01:55:52,121 --> 01:55:58,443
And the big sweep is a kind of that rises to that level.

1186
01:55:59,823 --> 01:56:11,985
But it seems like, I don't know, every single road project, every single paving project, if they don't knock on your door specifically and explain it to you before they do it,

1187
01:56:13,833 --> 01:56:16,434
I mean, did you really think they were going to do that?

1188
01:56:16,854 --> 01:56:24,076
It is why I'd be I'd be happy to to try and do more work on the commission's Facebook page.

1189
01:56:24,316 --> 01:56:32,299
Just, you know, kind of a block at a time, which is you're going to see be seeing more cyclists on Century Street going to the high school.

1190
01:56:32,319 --> 01:56:35,079
You're going to be seeing more on Whittier Street going to the high school.

1191
01:56:35,440 --> 01:56:42,682
Just just that level of of I mean, some of those like does

1192
01:56:43,462 --> 01:56:48,346
You know, if lots of people started biking down Whittier Street, is anybody on Whittier Street likely to complain?

1193
01:56:48,386 --> 01:56:53,470
Maybe they would, but I don't know.

1194
01:56:53,490 --> 01:56:58,655
But in other words, then at least we'll also have a record of communication to point to.

1195
01:56:58,675 --> 01:56:58,875
Yeah.

1196
01:57:02,158 --> 01:57:09,241
Yeah, nothing gets responses on an engagement on social media like discussion about infrastructure, for sure.

1197
01:57:09,361 --> 01:57:11,342
That's what people like to see.

1198
01:57:11,962 --> 01:57:16,404
And for all the whining that we see on, whining may be a pejorative term.

1199
01:57:16,724 --> 01:57:18,445
I should perhaps use something else.

1200
01:57:18,505 --> 01:57:26,168
The dissatisfaction with infrastructure changes that gets vocalized on social media is a,

1201
01:57:28,567 --> 01:57:34,909
For every comment that you see like that, and there's a lot of them, it does appear to be kind of a vocal-ish minority of people.

1202
01:57:34,949 --> 01:57:39,510
There's an awful lot of voices in favor of these sorts of things.

1203
01:57:40,390 --> 01:57:52,714
And sometimes it is a handful of people like kind of commenting a lot, but like, if you look at the engagement with those posts, those get an awful lot of positive attention, which is always like kind of a comforting sign, you know?

1204
01:57:53,828 --> 01:57:55,750
I think people do actually want these things.

1205
01:57:55,990 --> 01:57:59,472
They may not know where to look for them, but when they see them, they like them.

1206
01:58:01,054 --> 01:58:04,116
And God, look at the families with cargo bikes at the farmer's market.

1207
01:58:04,797 --> 01:58:06,758
People are riding their bikes there and bringing their families.

1208
01:58:06,898 --> 01:58:08,860
That is a win.

1209
01:58:08,880 --> 01:58:13,664
Do we have a motion to adjourn?

1210
01:58:14,885 --> 01:58:15,385
So moved.

1211
01:58:15,485 --> 01:58:15,946
So moved.

1212
01:58:17,347 --> 01:58:18,067
Thanks, everyone.

1213
01:58:18,087 --> 01:58:19,008
All right.

1214
01:58:19,068 --> 01:58:19,609
All in favor?

1215
01:58:19,629 --> 01:58:20,990
Aye.

1216
01:58:21,310 --> 01:58:21,370
Aye.

1217
01:58:24,122 --> 01:58:24,723
Thank you, Sam.

1218
01:58:25,064 --> 01:58:25,845
Meeting adjourned.

1219
01:58:26,245 --> 01:58:27,107
Thank you for coming.

